{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c8a00ada-273c-41dd-9ae6-61104d11266f","content":"It's a straightforward change. In your project file, either **remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property or set it to `false`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` defaults to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`), so no additional packages are needed.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of:\n\n1. **Running tests** — Use `dotnet test` as usual, but the underlying runner changes. You can also run the test executable directly (`./MyTests.exe`).\n2. **CLI options** — Platform-specific CLI flags differ from VSTest (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--filter` still, but other switches change). Run `dotnet test -- --help` to see them.\n3. **`.runsettings`** — Still supported, but some VSTest-specific settings may not apply.\n4. **Extensions** — If you use VSTest adapters/extensions, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n\nAfter the change, rebuild and run your tests to confirm everything works:\n\n```bash\ndotnet build\ndotnet test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f14e2db-2593-4b94-a949-2f6f9130804d","outputTokens":331,"requestId":"083C:E2933:7DA6D12:8BD8301:69EABE7B"},"id":"447acff6-d496-45fd-b77c-596e68a8dcc1","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:17.654Z","parentId":"e1c328cd-ce14-4ab0-9260-e99ef2d9ab7d"}
